books.title: Amp It Up
books.author: Frank Slootman
takeaways: Amp it Up means raise standards and expectations - never half-ass anything, always overdeliver
Hire for grit, drive, and learning speed - these matter more than credentials
Focus on the SINGLE most important thing and eliminate noise - clarity over consensus
Execution >>>>> Strategy - be a driver with personal ownership, not a passive passenger
Be quick to fire and weed out - culture is made by what and who you tolerate

books.title: How to Win Friends and Influence People
books.author: Dale Carnegie
takeaways: Don't criticize, condemn, or complain - change people's attitudes by changing yours first
Give honest and sincere appreciation - look for the good in people and tell them
Remember and use people's names - it's fundamental to building relationships
Be a great listener and show genuine interest - listening is as important as speaking
Smile and bring energy to every interaction - happiness depends on mental attitude, not circumstances
Be patient and make people feel valued - every person is superior to you in some way
